The key insight: for a ReLU network `f(x) = A2 * ReLU(A1*x + b1) + b2`, each hidden neuron `j` is active when `(A1_j · x + b1_j) > 0`. When only one neuron is active, the output is `A2_j * (A1_j · x + b1_j) + b2`, which is linear in x. By probing different regions of input space where different subsets of neurons are active, I can recover the linear pieces and thus recover the weight vectors.

